++ Tabs Windows Are The Same

Tabs and Windows are often regarded as separate objects in ConventionalSystems. This is a mistake as it reduces the level of control that is available to [Users].

    * Aids GrainedControl
    * Viewing resource requirements of applications through tabs and Windows
    * Especially useful in [Browser] to avoid embedded applications like Flash from wasting resources

++Implementation

RepresentationSubstitution essentially means that [Tabs] and [SystemWindows] would essentially be different representations of the same thing, the application's interface.